Fourteen white cubes are put together to form the figure on the right.  The complete surface of the figure, including the bottom, is painted red.  The figure is then separated into individual cubes.  How many of the individual cubes have exactly four red faces?

[asy]
size(150);
pair a=(1,0),b=(0,1),c=(0.45,0.4);

void drawcube(pair loc){
     filldraw(loc+b--loc--loc+a--loc+a+c--loc+a+b+c--loc+b+c--cycle,white);
     draw(loc+b--loc+a+b--loc+a+b+c^^loc+a+b--loc+a);
}

pair location[]={origin,b,a,2a,3a,3a+b,-c,3a-c,-2c,-2c+b,-2c+a,-2c+2a,-2c+3a,-2c+3a+b};

for(int i; i<14;++i){
   drawcube(location[i]);
}


[/asy]

Regions $A, B, C, J$ and $K$ represent ponds. Logs leave pond $A$ and float down flumes (represented by arrows) to eventually end up in pond $B$ or pond $C$. On leaving a pond, the logs are equally likely to use any available exit flume. Logs can only float in the direction the arrow is pointing. What is the probability that a log in pond $A$ will end up in pond $B$? Express your answer as a common fraction.

[asy]
label("$A$",(10,22),S);
label("$B$",(10,2),S);
label("$C$",(10,-7),S);
label("$J$",(2,13),S);
label("$K$",(10,12),S);
path a=(10,-10)..(20,0)--(0,0)..cycle;
path b=(10,-7)..(3,0)--(17,0)..cycle;
